			<CASNumber>9002-86-2</CASNumber>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Polyvinyl chloride (PVC) is a significant plastic derived from petroleum, widely used in everyday items. The recycling of PVC is challenging due to its high chlorine content and hazardous additives. However, it can be recycled into various products, including flooring, roofing, wall coverings, and automotive parts. PVC is made by reacting chlorine, carbon, and ethylene together to create a compound called Vinyl Chloride Monomer, which then undergoes polymerisation to result in base PVC.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">聚氯乙烯（PVC）是一种从石油中提炼出来的重要塑料，广泛应用于日常用品中。由于氯含量高且含有有害添加剂，聚氯乙烯的回收具有挑战性。不过，它可以被回收制成各种产品，包括地板、屋顶、墙面材料和汽车零件。聚氯乙烯是由氯、碳和乙烯反应生成一种叫做氯乙烯单体的化合物，然后经过聚合反应生成聚氯乙烯基体。</common:generalComment>
